What are special problems with the Broadcom chipset for advanced wireless? Why?
It becomes exspensive to install something that would provide wireless connection at a better quality
What are problems with Ralink?
Slow connection or drop outs in the signal
In Linux, how do you identify the chipset a dongle or card is using? [Hint: we've done it together on multiple days.]
Type Ifconfig in terminal.
What is Aircrack? What are its legal and illegal uses?
Network software suite consisting of a detector, packet sniffer, WEP and WPA/WPA2-PSK cracker and analysis tool; illegal to log packets or crack encryption keys.
What is airodump-ng? What does it do and what is it for?
Used for packet capturing of raw 802.11 frames;	collects data for use with aircrack.
What is aireplay-ng? What does it do and what is it for?
Used to inject frames; it generates traffic for later use.
What is a BSSID?
The MAC address of the wireless access point.
With regards to WEP - what is frame injection? How and why is it done?
Injecting traffic into other people's traffic to incriminate someone.
What does ARP stand for? How would one generate ARP packets on a network?
Address Resolution Protocol; 
